  <brief_title>Sleep Disturbance in Lung Cancer Patients.</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>University Hospital, Angers</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>University Hospital, Angers</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to 1-evaluate subjectively by questionnaires and objectively by
      ambulatory actigraphy the quality of sleep in patients with newly diagnosed lung cancer; 2-
      to correlate sleep quality index with quality of life, daytime alertness, Performans status
      and lung cancer staging at diagnosis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
